: Advantages of Feature Engineering & Feature Registry
Feature Engineering
Improves predictive power by converting raw data into model-ready signals
Reduces noise and highlights meaningful behavioural patterns
Enables point-in-time correct features, helping prevent data leakage
Creates reusable features across PD, application, and behavioural models
Standardises logic for rolling windows, ratios, trends, and aggregations
Improves explainability because business logic is clearer than raw inputs
Supports consistency between training, backtesting, and production scoring
Helps align model inputs with business definitions and risk policy
Feature Registry
Provides a central catalogue of available features
Documents feature meaning, owner, lineage, and calculation logic
Improves discoverability so teams do not rebuild the same features
Supports versioning for auditability and reproducibility
Clarifies approved versus deprecated features
Strengthens governance through ownership and control
Makes model review and validation easier for risk and compliance teams
Speeds up onboarding for ML engineers, analysts, and validators
Business value
Faster model development
Better governance and control
Higher consistency across teams
Easier regulatory and audit review
